title: Elite Athletics and Fitness Time Trial Series
Le Tour de Sainte Genevieve-Kids Race
Tour of Kansas City
description: 48th Annual Tour of Kansas City.  3 Criteriums in Kansas City metro area.  Overall $10,000 prize list.  $1000 in omnium bonuses divided among top 5 pro,1,2 overall.
course:
New Longview Criterium - Friday criterium next to Longview Community College.  Multiple turns and limited elevation gain.

Saturday and Sunday criteriums run on Kansas City Missouri Police driving course.  Each day will have a different configuration that is similar to typical criterium courses.  Great roads, lots of turns, mostly flat with one small hill.
registration: Online registration closes at midnight on 6/21.  $10 late fee for race day registration.  Multi-race discount when registering online.  Race day registration opens 1 hour prior to first race and closes 30 minutes prior to each race.  Event held under USA Cycling Permit 2011-1150.  Online registration at TBD link (USA Cycling site).  For more event information visit www.tourofkc.com
notes: CPSC approved helmet required. No sleeveless jerseys. Free lap rule applies. Promoter reserves right to combine or alter races. Wheel pit provided (not neutral). Riders must have annual USAC license or purchase 1-day USAC license. Registration fee includes $3 USAC insurance and any KCA/MOBAR surcharges.
directions:
New Longview Crit in Lee\'s Summit, MO.  Located at Longview Community College.  Take I-470 to View High Drive.  Go south on View High Dr. to 3rd St.  Turn right and follow signs to Longview College parking lot.

Kansas City Police Academy course - 6885 Pleasant Valley Rd, Kansas City, MO - Take I-435 north (on Missouri side) to exit 51 (3 miles north of Worlds of Fun).  Go southwest (left) on Shoal Creek Parkway to Pleasant Valley Road.  Go left (east) on Pleasant Valley Rd and turn right just past Police Academy building.

title: Alpine Shop Short Track  Crit Series
Svitak Freedom Ride Time Trial
description: Brand new in 2011 is the addition of a time trial. This is a USA Cycling permitted race. It will be held on Friday evening before the rides on Saturday. The route is famous in Joplin, its Reinmiller loop 18.2 miles. Wind and hills you’ll wish you’d never met, there is a 4 mile section (Reinmiller road) of approx 13 climbs. Finish line is 4 miles short of the start so you\'ll ride your bike back to the finish line following the road markings.
